  <data name="swagger_remarks_automationinterpreter_sendcodigosbarras" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Description:
         
             Based on the data provided, it notifies the automation of the creation, overwriting or deletion of barcodes.
             
             When consuming this API, the Automation Manager includes an "X-Hub-Signature" HTTP header that contains the JSON hash of the incoming parameter
             calculated from the "HMACSHA512" algorithm and a secret shared with the client application that makes this API available.
             The specific implementation of this API may use the aforementioned header to verify the authenticity of the received message.
             To do this, it recalculates the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and secret shared with the Automation Manager.
             and checks that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
             
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
  <data name="swagger_remarks_automationinterpreter_sendentrada" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Based on the data provided, it notifies the entry of stock to the automation.
         
