             To do this, it recalculates the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and secret shared with the Automation Manager.
             and checks that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
         
             Decimals must be sent with '.'.
             The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
